about.description:
Google Cloud Build API is a Google Cloud service that lets client applications create and manage builds on Google Cloud Platform. Cloud Build lets you build software quickly across all languages. Get complete control over defining custom workflows for building, testing, and deploying across multiple environments such as VMs, serverless, Kubernetes, or Firebase.
See the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/cloudbuild/latest/index.html#quick-start).
about.summary: Google Cloud Build API client library

name: google-cloud-build
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "google-cloud-build" %}
{% set version = "3.23.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/google-cloud-build-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6e8dd88cb816f30bb55cec1e4d2285d570a223d34df516fb017a495ed605720e

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - google-api-core >=1.34.1,<3.0.0dev,!=2.0.*,!=2.1.*,!=2.2.*,!=2.3.*,!=2.4.*,!=2.5.*,!=2.6.*,!=2.7.*,!=2.8.*,!=2.9.*,!=2.10.*
    - google-api-core-grpc
    - google-auth >=2.14.1,<3.0.0dev,!=2.24.0,!=2.25.0
    - grpc-google-iam-v1 >=0.12.4,<1.0.0dev
    - proto-plus >=1.22.3,<2.0.0dev
    - protobuf >=3.19.5,<5.0.0dev,!=3.20.0,!=3.20.1,!=4.21.0,!=4.21.1,!=4.21.2,!=4.21.3,!=4.21.4,!=4.21.5

test:
  imports:
    - grpc
    - google.cloud.devtools.cloudbuild
    - google.cloud.devtools.cloudbuild_v1
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-python/tree/main/packages/google-cloud-build
  summary: Google Cloud Build API client library
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  description: "Google Cloud Build API is a Google Cloud service that lets client applications create and manage builds on Google Cloud Platform. Cloud Build lets you build software quickly across all languages. Get complete control over defining custom workflows for building, testing, and deploying across multiple environments
    such as VMs, serverless, Kubernetes, or Firebase.\nSee the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/cloudbuild/latest/index.html#quick-start)."

  doc_url: https://googleapis.dev/python/cloudbuild/latest/index.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/googleapis/python-cloudbuild

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xylar
    - parthea
